## Concept and Initial Learning Log Analysis for Lecture Archive Summarization Platform

](/paper/Concept-and-Initial-Learning-Log-Analysis-for-Hasegawa-Liu/640717330e7bf63f9e4fa16662b2e836970d86a3)

[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)[Xiaoting Liu](/author/Xiaoting-Liu/2267861864)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)

## Object Recognition from Scientific Document Based on Compartment and Text Blocks Refinement Framework

](/paper/Object-Recognition-from-Scientific-Document-Based-Li-Gu/500138e7454bc803a6b559cbd3cd1e6da148ce6b)

[Jinghong Li](/author/Jinghong-Li/2267861843)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)

Computer Science

-   14 December 2023

A new document layout analysis framework called CTBR(Compartment&Text Blocks Refinement) is proposed, which defines scientific documents into hierarchical divisions: base domain, compartment, and text blocks, and utilizes the results of text block classification to implement object recognition within scientific documents based on rule-based compartment segmentation.

## An Automatic Focal Period Detection Architecture for Lecture Archives

](/paper/An-Automatic-Focal-Period-Detection-Architecture-Sheng-Ota/8151b1a9001eb898b8227257c7c3bd3cc53c114b)

[Ruozhu Sheng](/author/Ruozhu-Sheng/2179458405)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[S. Hasegawa](/author/S.-Hasegawa/2061606936)

Computer Science, Education

-   2022

This research divides lecture archives with high quality and fixed camera angles into 1-min segments, counts how many times students have accessed each segment from LMS as the label data, and defines the students’ focal periods, and proposes a deep neural network architecture for detecting focal periods for online students in lecture archives.

[

## A Text Block Refinement Framework For Text Classification and Object Recognition From Academic Articles

](/paper/A-Text-Block-Refinement-Framework-For-Text-and-From-Li-Ota/105bab95d71198984988b95f9e97877841059b46)

[Jinghong Li](/author/Jinghong-Li/2108991277)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[S. Hasegawa](/author/S.-Hasegawa/3001928)

Computer Science

-   27 May 2023

A novel Text Block Refinement Framework (TBRF) is developed, a machine learning and rule-based scheme hybrid that achieves over 95% classification accuracy and 90% detection accuracy for tables and figures in academic articles.

[

## Mining Collective Knowledge for Reconstructing Learning Resource

](/paper/Mining-Collective-Knowledge-for-Reconstructing-Ota-Kashihara/bb48a19bffe9095024dae69f49c2b54415fa58b7)

[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[A. Kashihara](/author/A.-Kashihara/2374708)

Computer Science, Education

-   2010

This paper proposes a collective knowledge mining method that can extract pages and links from learning histories gathered from a group of learners who learned the Web resources to reconstruct the hyperspace including useful pages and Links to be learned.

[

## A Survey Forest Diagram : Gain a Divergent Insight View on a Specific Research Topic

](/paper/A-Survey-Forest-Diagram-%3A-Gain-a-Divergent-Insight-Li-Gu/1277221119f7d5e5695fe3eeb778140a26fbac28)

[Jinghong Li](/author/Jinghong-Li/2267861843)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)

Computer Science, Education

-   24 July 2024

An in-depth Survey Forest Diagram is developed that guides novice researchers in divergent thinking about the research topic by indicating the citation clues among multiple papers, to help expand the survey perspective for novice researchers.

[

## Design of Voice Style Detection of Lecture Archives

](/paper/Design-of-Voice-Style-Detection-of-Lecture-Archives-Liu-Gu/c2853767109d41b8edd635f2444c451f64fb82cb)

[Xiaoting Liu](/author/Xiaoting-Liu/2267861864)[Wen Gu](/author/Wen-Gu/2191728751)[Koichi Ota](/author/Koichi-Ota/2000912578)[Shinobu Hasegawa](/author/Shinobu-Hasegawa/2267751251)

Computer Science

-   31 October 2023

This article describes the experimental dataset collection design considering individual differences and lecture room environments and summarizes how such efforts will be effective in realizing personalized voice style detection and improving the accuracy of speech processing in real environments.
